The ANC in KwaZulu Natal reaffirms its support for former president Jacob Zuma, as he prepares to appear in court on Wednesday on charges of fraud, corruption, racketeering and money laundering. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC in KZN has reaffirmed its support for former President Jacob Zuma. He's facing 16 charges relating to a multi-billion-rand arms deal. READ: ANC condemns senior members' behaviour The former president is due back in court on Wednesday. He is expected to plead not guilty to the charges and also challenge state advocate Billy Downer as he believes he may be biased.